 &lt;div style=&#34;font-size: 14px; margin: 0; padding: 0; width: 100%;&#34;&gt;&lt;p style=&#34;line-height: 160%; box-sizing: content-box; margin: 10px 0; color: #333;&#34;&gt;SELinux = Security Enhanced Linux&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;blockquote style=&#34;line-height: 160%; box-sizing: content-box; margin: 15px 0; border-left: 4px solid #ddd; padding: 0 15px; color: #777;&#34;&gt;
&lt;p style=&#34;line-height: 160%; box-sizing: content-box; margin: 10px 0; color: #333; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0;&#34;&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Security-Enhanced_Linux&#34; style=&#34;line-height: 160%; box-sizing: content-box; text-decoration: underline; color: #5286bc;&#34;&gt;Wiki: Security-Enhanced Linux&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;strong style=&#34;line-height: 160%; box-sizing: content-box; font-weight: 700;&#34;&gt;Security-Enhanced Linux (SELinux)&lt;/strong&gt; is a Linux kernel security module that provides a mechanism for supporting access control security policies, including mandatory access controls (MAC).&lt;br&gt;
SELinux is &lt;strong style=&#34;line-height: 160%; box-sizing: content-box; font-weight: 700;&#34;&gt;a set of kernel modifications&lt;/strong&gt; and &lt;strong style=&#34;line-height: 160%; box-sizing: content-box; font-weight: 700;&#34;&gt;user-space tools&lt;/strong&gt; that have been added to various Linux distributions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;p style=&#34;line-height: 160%; box-sizing: content-box; margin: 10px 0; color: #333;&#34;&gt;SELinux&amp;#x8D77;&amp;#x6E90;&amp;#x4E8E;&amp;#x7F8E;&amp;#x56FD;&amp;#x56FD;&amp;#x5B89;&amp;#x5C40;(NSA)&amp;#x3002;&amp;#x5B83;&amp;#x7684;&amp;#x524D;&amp;#x8EAB;&amp;#x662F;NSA&amp;#x7684;&amp;#x4E00;&amp;#x4E2A;&amp;#x53EB;Flask&amp;#x7684;&amp;#x9879;&amp;#x76EE;&amp;#xFF0C;&amp;#x540E;&amp;#x6765;&amp;#xFF0C;NSA&amp;#x89C9;&amp;#x5F97;Linux&amp;#x66F4;&amp;#x5177;&amp;#x53D1;&amp;#x5C55;&amp;#x548C;&amp;#x666E;&amp;#x53CA;&amp;#x524D;&amp;#x666F;&amp;#xFF0C;&amp;#x6240;&amp;#x4EE5;&amp;#x5C31;&amp;#x5728;Linux&amp;#x7CFB;&amp;#x7EDF;&amp;#x4E0A;&amp;#x91CD;&amp;#x65B0;&amp;#x5B9E;&amp;#x73B0;&amp;#x4E86;FLASK&amp;#xFF0C;&amp;#x79F0;&amp;#x4E4B;&amp;#x4E3A;SELinux&amp;#x3002;&lt;/p&gt;
